import React from 'react'
import Navbar from '../../components/navbar'
import {Segment, Container, Image, Divider, Icon, Grid} from 'semantic-ui-react'

const About = () => {
    return(
        <>
            <Navbar/>
            <Segment vertical>
                <Container text>
                    <Grid columns={2} relaxed='very stackable'>
                        <Grid.Column>
                            <Image src='secondBangkok.png' size='medium' circular />
                        </Grid.Column>
                        <Grid.Column>
                        <Divider horizontal>
                            <Icon name={"code"}/>
                            Experience
                        </Divider>                
                        <Image src='paypal.png' avatar/> Global Technical Support Engineer
                    <Divider horizontal>
                        <Icon name={"plug icon"}/>
                        Skills
                    </Divider>
                    <Image src='react.png' avatar/> React
                    <Image src='node.jpeg' avatar/> Node
                    <Image src='mongodb.jpeg' avatar/> MongoDB
                    <Image src='react.png' avatar/> React
                    <Image src='react.png' avatar/> React
                    <Divider horizontal>
                        <Icon name={"book"}/>
                        Education
                    </Divider>
                    Education
                        </Grid.Column>
                    </Grid>
                    <Divider horizontal>
                        <Icon name={"map marker alternate"}/>
                        Chicago
                    </Divider>
                    I am currently working as an API Support and Migrations Specialist for  PayPal, servicing our Braintree product. 
                </Container>
            </Segment>
        </>
    )
}

export default About
